          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Four different sets of the samples In and Al foils of",
                "size 1.0 X 1.0 cm2 with 99.97% purity were wrapped",
                "individually with 0.025-mm-thick Al foils. The",
                "weights for different sample are",
                "Proton Energy      In sample Mass        Al sample Mass",
                " (MeV)                 (g)                   (g)",
                "         13                 0.243                 0.033",
                "         16                 0.186                 0.047",
                "         19                 0.181                 0.054",
                "         22                 0.239                 0.052"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A pre-calibrated 80 cm3 HPGe detector was",
                "coupled to a PC-based 4094 channel analyzer.",
                "The resolution of detector system during counting was",
                "measured to be 1.80 at 1332.50 keV gamma line of 60Co."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The irradiation for each separated stack of",
                "Al-In has been carried out at specific neutron",
                "energies for about ~10 hours."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "P-LI7"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The natural lithium foil of thickness 6.80",
                "mg/cm2 was wrapped with tantalum foil, ~3.20 mg/cm2",
                "has been placed before the Li target facing the",
                "proton beam, while a relatively Ta foil was used at the",
                "back of the Li foil to stop the proton beam.",
                "The proton beam energies were 13, 16, 19 and 22 MeV."
              ]
            }
          ],
